d which bow should I use to go with what I max out?  Please help if you can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viirruss>Viirruss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#660000>(12/9/02 6:50:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=514.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Confused on Bow</span><hr size=1> From build notes 14.6:<br>
&quot;We found some inconsistencies in the type of initiative used with bows. We have now fixed the existing bows and crossbows, and the following should be the overall rule: - All weapons with &quot;Bow&quot; as primary attack skill will depend on Physical Initiative. - All Bow-type weapons using &quot;Rifle&quot; as primary attack skill will depend on Ranged Init. The latter applies to crossbows. As part of the process we have changed the main attack skill on certain crossbows that used &quot;bow&quot;. They will now all use &quot;rifle&quot; instead. Most bows and crossbows have had their damage improved, and some have also got additional skill modifiers. In addition we have lowered the equip-time on some bows. - It has been mentioned before, but again: Only Bows using &quot;Bow&quot; as their main attack skill will be able to fire Special Arrows. This means no crossbows can fire them.&quot;<br>
Hope that helps...<br>
